    "body": "<header>\n\n<video controls=\"controls\" poster=\"https://mediasrv.churchofjesuschrist.org/media-services/GA/videoStill/6275399234001\" thumbnail=\"https://mediasrv.churchofjesuschrist.org/media-services/GA/thumbnail/6275399234001\" data-video-title=\"Michael A. Dunn\" data-video-description=\"Elder Michael A. Dunn speaks at the 191st Semiannual General Conference of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints on October 2-3, 2021.\" data-video-id=\"6275399234001\" data-ip=\"Download &amp; Streaming\" data-duration=\"601000\" data-assetId=\"C4937040919A2870EDDFAB81B2AC1F8BEE0B4470\" data-ref-id=\"C4937040919A2870EDDFAB81B2AC1F8BEE0B4470\" id=\"video2\"><source src=\"https://mediasrv.churchofjesuschrist.org/media-services/GA/type/6275399234001/hls.m3u8\" type=\"application/vnd.apple.mpegurl\"/><source src=\"https://mediasrv.churchofjesuschrist.org/media-services/GA/size/6275399234001/640/360/993000\" type=\"video/mp4\" data-width=\"640\" data-height=\"360\" data-file-size=\"74798789\"/><source src=\"https://mediasrv.churchofjesuschrist.org/media-services/GA/size/6275399234001/1280/720/2126000\" type=\"video/mp4\" data-width=\"1280\" data-height=\"720\" data-file-size=\"159915536\"/><source src=\"https://media2.ldscdn.org/assets/general-conference/october-2021-general-conference/2021-10-5040-michael-a-dunn-1080p-eng.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-file-size=\"198279348\"/><\/video><h1 data-aid=\"147979947\" id=\"title1\">One Percent Better<\/h1>\n<div class=\"byline\">\n<p class=\"author-name\" data-aid=\"147979953\" id=\"author1\">By Elder Michael A. Dunn<\/p>\n<p class=\"author-role\" data-aid=\"147979959\" id=\"author2\">Of the Seventy<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<p class=\"kicker\" data-aid=\"147979965\" id=\"kicker1\">Every effort to change we make\u2014no matter how tiny it seems to us\u2014just might make the biggest difference in our lives.<\/p>\n<\/header>\n<div class=\"body-block\">\n<p data-aid=\"147979971\" id=\"p1\">For more than a century, the national bicycle racing teams of Great Britain had been the laughingstock of the cycling world. Mired in mediocrity, British riders had managed only a handful of gold medals in 100 years of Olympic competitions and had been even more underwhelming in cycling\u2019s marquee event, the three-week long Tour de France\u2014where no British rider had prevailed in 110 years. So sorry was the plight of British riders that some bike manufacturers refused to even sell bikes to the Brits, fearing it would forever sully their hard-won reputations. And despite devoting enormous resources into cutting-edge technology and every newfangled training regimen, nothing worked.<\/p>\n<img id=\"img1\" src=\"https://assets.ldscdn.org/00/9c/009c994322d1774d7d089abc39c5e08f09b64eaf/olympiics_cyclist_1908.png\" data-img-id=\"5d427a4c22f911ec81b6eeeeac1e0e28bd0e8f0a\" srcset=\"https://assets.ldscdn.org/ca/d6/cad63645d336349bc8a76ee51055c1b941798b3a/olympiics_cyclist_1908.png 60w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/c7/08/c70817aecb4017e5823ded70dda5de01828e750b/olympiics_cyclist_1908.png 100w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/e9/42/e9427f643d4876874b22ef2380977d78e790e970/olympiics_cyclist_1908.png 200w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/43/0c/430c1932473097711de2e51d8e0252b5a0a9c3d0/olympiics_cyclist_1908.png 250w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/44/9e/449ee97540eae3ca5c7782d7b140c5a4dc4d21cf/olympiics_cyclist_1908.png 320w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/00/9c/009c994322d1774d7d089abc39c5e08f09b64eaf/olympiics_cyclist_1908.png 500w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/e9/b5/e9b5774ed11ca5aa1dcb89d91c1a9c4ec6bf8fa4/olympiics_cyclist_1908.png 640w\" data-assetId=\"5d427a4c22f911ec81b6eeeeac1e0e28bd0e8f0a\" data-missing-asset=\"false\" data-width=\"500\" data-height=\"323\" data-aspect-ratio=\"1.5479876160990713\" alt=\"Olympic Cyclists\"/>\n<p data-aid=\"147979977\" id=\"p2\">Nothing, that is, until 2003, when a small, largely unnoticed change occurred that would forever alter the trajectory of British cycling. That new approach would also reveal an eternal principle\u2014with a promise\u2014regarding our ofttimes perplexing mortal quest to improve ourselves. So what happened in British cycling that has great relevance to our personal pursuit to be better daughters and sons of God?<\/p>\n<p data-aid=\"147979983\" id=\"p3\">In 2003, Sir Dave Brailsford was hired. Unlike previous coaches who attempted dramatic, overnight turnarounds, Sir Brailsford instead committed to a strategy he referred to as \u201cthe aggregation of marginal gains.\u201d This entailed implementing small improvements in everything. That meant constantly measuring key statistics and targeting specific weaknesses.<\/p>\n<p data-aid=\"147979989\" id=\"p14\">It\u2019s somewhat akin to the prophet Samuel the Lamanite\u2019s notion of \u201cwalk[ing] circumspectly.\u201d<a class=\"note-ref\" href=\"#note1\"><sup class=\"marker\">1<\/sup><\/a> This broader, more holistic view avoids the trap of being myopically fixated on just the obvious problem or sin at hand. Said Brailsford, \u201cThe whole principle came from the idea that if you broke down everything you could think of that goes into riding a bike, and then improved it by 1 percent, you will get a significant increase when you put them all together.\u201d<a class=\"note-ref\" href=\"#note2\"><sup class=\"marker\">2<\/sup><\/a><\/p>\n<p data-aid=\"147979998\" id=\"p4\">His approach aligns well with that of the Lord, who taught us the criticalness of the 1 percent\u2014even at the expense of the 99 percent. Of course, He was teaching the gospel imperative to seek out individuals in need. But what if we applied that same principle to the very sweet and savory second principle of the gospel, repentance? Rather than being stymied by the churn and dramatic swings between sin and repentance, what if our approach was to narrow our focus\u2014even as we broadened it? Instead of trying to perfect everything, what if we tackled just one thing?<\/p>\n<p data-aid=\"147980003\" id=\"p15\">For example, what if in your new wide-angle awareness, you discover you have neglected a daily reading of the Book of Mormon? Well, instead of desperately plowing through all 531 pages in one night, what if we committed instead to read just 1 percent of it\u2014that\u2019s just five pages a day\u2014or another manageable goal for your situation? Could aggregating small but steady <em>marginal gains<\/em> in our lives finally be the way to victory over even the most pesky of our personal shortcomings? Can this bite-sized approach to tackling our blemishes really work?<\/p>\n<p data-aid=\"147980008\" id=\"p5\">Well, acclaimed author James Clear says this strategy puts the math squarely in our favor. He maintains that \u201chabits are the \u2018compound interest of self-improvement.\u2019 If you can get just one percent better at something each day, by the end of a year \u2026 you will be 37 times better.\u201d<a class=\"note-ref\" href=\"#note3\"><sup class=\"marker\">3<\/sup><\/a><\/p>\n<p data-aid=\"147980013\" id=\"p7\">Brailsford\u2019s small gains began with the obvious, such as equipment, kit fabrics, and training patterns. But his team didn\u2019t stop there. They continued to find 1 percent improvements in overlooked and unexpected areas such as nutrition and even maintenance nuances. Over time, these myriads of micro-betterments aggregated into stunning results, which came faster than anyone could have imagined. Truly, they were onto the eternal principle of \u201cline upon line, precept upon precept, here a little and there a little.\u201d<a class=\"note-ref\" href=\"#note4\"><sup class=\"marker\">4<\/sup><\/a><\/p>\n<p data-aid=\"147980018\" id=\"p8\">Will little adjustments work that \u201cmighty change\u201d<a class=\"note-ref\" href=\"#note5\"><sup class=\"marker\">5<\/sup><\/a> that you desire? Properly implemented, I\u2019m 99 percent certain they will! But the one caveat with this approach is that for small gains to aggregate, there must be a consistent, day-in and day-out effort. And although we won\u2019t likely be perfect, we must be determined to mirror our persistence with patience. Do that, and the sweet rewards of increased righteousness will bring you the joy and peace you seek. As President Russell M. Nelson has taught: \u201cNothing is more liberating, more ennobling, or more crucial to our individual progression than is a regular, daily focus on repentance. Repentance is not an event; it is a process. It is the key to happiness and peace of mind. When coupled with faith, repentance opens our access to the power of the Atonement of Jesus Christ.\u201d<a class=\"note-ref\" href=\"#note6\"><sup class=\"marker\">6<\/sup><\/a><\/p>\n<img id=\"img2\" src=\"https://assets.ldscdn.org/78/66/78667b8979a855dd9486ff2b85529f2e91df4da4/hand_mustard_seed_faith.png\" data-img-id=\"6056956b22f911ec9229eeeeac1e27960081fa36\" srcset=\"https://assets.ldscdn.org/06/0e/060eefe526169870b013248a17709053bb7ac478/hand_mustard_seed_faith.png 60w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/0a/88/0a88a19717e7da8af3c1d01cec51b110a52db5ed/hand_mustard_seed_faith.png 100w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/77/bd/77bd27cbd7df03bb6a4422a4cdc0e6d81462fd04/hand_mustard_seed_faith.png 200w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/eb/7f/eb7f4106360e07e878bc9515faa619017b0106eb/hand_mustard_seed_faith.png 250w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/3c/96/3c96342f78791a9758bb92f77fc0f9a4199546a8/hand_mustard_seed_faith.png 320w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/78/66/78667b8979a855dd9486ff2b85529f2e91df4da4/hand_mustard_seed_faith.png 500w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/00/45/00452bc242bbce67d23488c76a3644a5d129c69d/hand_mustard_seed_faith.png 640w\" data-assetId=\"6056956b22f911ec9229eeeeac1e27960081fa36\" data-missing-asset=\"false\" data-width=\"500\" data-height=\"323\" data-aspect-ratio=\"1.5479876160990713\" alt=\"Hand\"/>\n<img id=\"img3\" src=\"https://assets.ldscdn.org/8b/c0/8bc0dbc3ef244339d6bbe093e6f7fa0a2db32a5f/acacia_tree.png\" data-img-id=\"6013e71a22f911ec9229eeeeac1e2796cb24516f\" srcset=\"https://assets.ldscdn.org/45/51/45510e8b7481916908f8961a593a1bb19dbb6ef6/acacia_tree.png 60w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/d0/ef/d0ef93f810e2b3e4ee5c271dcca5feb01f7de80d/acacia_tree.png 100w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/d1/ea/d1ea6b43686ecf4f74d7c32374542a37f5422afe/acacia_tree.png 200w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/84/f0/84f08f0d5609cfd017f452af00e08aa2adbe710e/acacia_tree.png 250w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/7d/ae/7dae3a3c7a1fe1c4616f77988795a2b72313d720/acacia_tree.png 320w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/8b/c0/8bc0dbc3ef244339d6bbe093e6f7fa0a2db32a5f/acacia_tree.png 500w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/d8/dd/d8dd1cd87a743b5055275e5779c8c6a5b42d3261/acacia_tree.png 640w\" data-assetId=\"6013e71a22f911ec9229eeeeac1e2796cb24516f\" data-missing-asset=\"false\" data-width=\"500\" data-height=\"323\" data-aspect-ratio=\"1.5479876160990713\" alt=\"Acacia Tree\"/>\n<p data-aid=\"147980023\" id=\"p9\">As to repentance\u2019s prerequisite of faith, the scriptures are clear. All that\u2019s initially required is a mere \u201cparticle of faith.\u201d<a class=\"note-ref\" href=\"#note7\"><sup class=\"marker\">7<\/sup><\/a> And if we can muster this \u201cmustard seed\u201d<a class=\"note-ref\" href=\"#note8\"><sup class=\"marker\">8<\/sup><\/a> mentality, we too can expect unexpected and exceptional improvements in our lives. But remember, just as we would not attempt to go from being Attila the Hun to Mother Teresa overnight, so too should we reorient our patterns of improvement incrementally. Even if the changes needed in your life are wholesale, begin at a small scale. That\u2019s especially true if you are feeling overwhelmed or discouraged.<\/p>\n<p data-aid=\"147980028\" id=\"p16\">This process is not always accomplished in a linear fashion. Even among the most determined there may be setbacks. Having experienced the frustration of this in my own life, I know that it can sometimes feel like 1 percent forward and 2 percent back. Yet if we remain undaunted in our determination to consistently eke out those 1 percent gains, He who has \u201ccarried our sorrows\u201d<a class=\"note-ref\" href=\"#note9\"><sup class=\"marker\">9<\/sup><\/a> will surely carry us.<\/p>\n<p data-aid=\"147980033\" id=\"p10\">Obviously, if we are involved in grievous sins, the Lord is clear and unequivocal; we need to stop, get help from our bishop, and turn away from such practices immediately. But as Elder David A. Bednar enjoined: \u201cSmall, steady, incremental spiritual improvements are the steps the Lord would have us take. Preparing to walk guiltless before God is one of the primary purposes of mortality and the pursuit of a lifetime; it does not result from sporadic spurts of intense spiritual activity.\u201d<a class=\"note-ref\" href=\"#note10\"><sup class=\"marker\">10<\/sup><\/a><\/p>\n<img id=\"img4\" src=\"https://assets.ldscdn.org/42/6c/426c72a6d2f405f3895534cec340be89292eae62/olympics_cyclists_tour_de_france.png\" data-img-id=\"61e0454722f911eca865eeeeac1e3df95d4de79d\" srcset=\"https://assets.ldscdn.org/05/28/0528cfc9b20cb1c20f5f8d30a9e38ec910fecf27/olympics_cyclists_tour_de_france.png 60w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/88/30/88306a072588b3c773b66446f13ec998957399d9/olympics_cyclists_tour_de_france.png 100w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/26/31/2631bbdd81c199e69becb99fd880db51eaaae824/olympics_cyclists_tour_de_france.png 200w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/73/d1/73d17f87563693fdcbf9df0b5942b38d96fa83f1/olympics_cyclists_tour_de_france.png 250w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/6e/3d/6e3d753135c40084c5632d9db67cc66642f5c50c/olympics_cyclists_tour_de_france.png 320w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/42/6c/426c72a6d2f405f3895534cec340be89292eae62/olympics_cyclists_tour_de_france.png 500w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/39/d7/39d71cd700a7745db83ee3fafc3b730865ed6ca6/olympics_cyclists_tour_de_france.png 640w\" data-assetId=\"61e0454722f911eca865eeeeac1e3df95d4de79d\" data-missing-asset=\"false\" data-width=\"500\" data-height=\"323\" data-aspect-ratio=\"1.5479876160990713\" alt=\"Tour de France\"/>\n<p data-aid=\"147980038\" id=\"p11\">So, does this pocket-sized approach to repentance and real change really work? Is the proof in the pedaling, so to speak? Consider what\u2019s happened to British cycling in the past two decades since implementing this philosophy. British cyclists have now won the storied Tour de France an astonishing six times. During the past four Olympic Games, Great Britain has been the most successful country across all cycling disciplines. And in the recently concluded Tokyo Olympics, the UK won more gold medals in cycling than any other country.<\/p>\n<figure class=\"image no-print\" id=\"figure1\">\n<img id=\"img5\" src=\"https://assets.ldscdn.org/dc/97/dc97f37f29beb210498a88e25d193c387df773df/athletes_olympic_composite.png\" data-img-id=\"5e03325322f911ecaf29eeeeac1e4444676fb311\" srcset=\"https://assets.ldscdn.org/8d/3c/8d3ce63eb3fee25ca01c0215e813298093184596/athletes_olympic_composite.png 60w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/b6/f3/b6f3720e0676770ea401ec0054e514bba5572f07/athletes_olympic_composite.png 100w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/c2/8d/c28d3d6795a35da6fa723e706594153ac8f33e45/athletes_olympic_composite.png 200w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/cf/3a/cf3a8b5b174ee0fb80cf083df2608e7cbff83780/athletes_olympic_composite.png 250w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/36/3d/363d63c685818553e2f3ce7cab07bc5353501d0e/athletes_olympic_composite.png 320w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/dc/97/dc97f37f29beb210498a88e25d193c387df773df/athletes_olympic_composite.png 500w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/c1/90/c1903f509521a8654498270ff6ae0327416fae41/athletes_olympic_composite.png 640w\" data-assetId=\"5e03325322f911ecaf29eeeeac1e4444676fb311\" data-missing-asset=\"false\" data-width=\"500\" data-height=\"323\" data-aspect-ratio=\"1.5479876160990713\" alt=\"Olympics\"/>\n<div class=\"credit\">\n<p data-aid=\"148063273\" id=\"figure1_p1\">Photographs of British cyclists by (clockwise from top left) Friedemann Vogel, John Giles, and Greg Baker/Getty Images<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/figure>\n<p data-aid=\"147980042\" id=\"p12\">But far outshining worldly silver or gold, our precious promise down our roadway to the eternities is that we will indeed \u201ctriumph in Christ.\u201d<a class=\"note-ref\" href=\"#note11\"><sup class=\"marker\">11<\/sup><\/a> And as we commit to making small but steady improvements, we are promised \u201ca crown of glory that fadeth not away.\u201d<a class=\"note-ref\" href=\"#note12\"><sup class=\"marker\">12<\/sup><\/a> With basking in that undimmable luster beckoning, I invite you to examine your life and see what\u2019s stagnated or slowed you on the covenant pathway. Then look broader. Seek modest but makeable fixes in your life that might result in the sweet joy of being just a little better.<\/p>\n<p data-aid=\"147980046\" id=\"p17\">Remember, David used just one small stone to take down a seemingly invincible giant. But he had four other stones at the ready. Similarly, Alma the Younger\u2019s wicked disposition and eternal destiny were altered by just one simple, salient thought\u2014a remembrance of his father\u2019s teachings about the saving grace of Jesus Christ. And so it is with our Savior, who, though sinless, \u201creceived not of the fulness at first, but continued from grace to grace, until he received a fulness.\u201d<a class=\"note-ref\" href=\"#note13\"><sup class=\"marker\">13<\/sup><\/a><\/p>\n<img id=\"img6\" src=\"https://assets.ldscdn.org/c6/67/c66782bed929986caf03593f6cc0b7994daa045b/christ_rich_man_art_hoffman.png\" data-img-id=\"54cf8b6622f911ecb34aeeeeac1e8d8a0aa41f27\" srcset=\"https://assets.ldscdn.org/c7/03/c7030038023ff1a0d453c598d88271eb53c4bce8/christ_rich_man_art_hoffman.png 60w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/fc/81/fc81b925265c4e9729c36a3b2b255b9b5f03f2a6/christ_rich_man_art_hoffman.png 100w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/60/9d/609d08bb1d460367b2c22e871691998a1c7e1171/christ_rich_man_art_hoffman.png 200w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/67/f1/67f11b0d9ebff93d523ca1dca6ccac9ccfebc46e/christ_rich_man_art_hoffman.png 250w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/25/63/25633de787dcd0ebf4e5bf5daff17a96165e3e6f/christ_rich_man_art_hoffman.png 320w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/c6/67/c66782bed929986caf03593f6cc0b7994daa045b/christ_rich_man_art_hoffman.png 500w,https://assets.ldscdn.org/6f/f2/6ff2788256c8fcb3e52cad4c41806c52415abdac/christ_rich_man_art_hoffman.png 640w\" data-assetId=\"54cf8b6622f911ecb34aeeeeac1e8d8a0aa41f27\" data-missing-asset=\"false\" data-width=\"500\" data-height=\"323\" data-aspect-ratio=\"1.5479876160990713\" alt=\"Christ and the Rich Young Ruler\"/>\n<p data-aid=\"147980049\" id=\"p13\">It is He who knows when a sparrow falls that is likewise focused on the minute as well as the momentous moments in our lives and who is ready right now to assist you in whatever your 1 percent quest is coming out of this conference. Because every effort to change we make\u2014no matter how tiny it seems to us\u2014just might make the biggest difference in our lives.<\/p>\n<p data-aid=\"147980053\" id=\"p18\">To this end, Elder Neal A. Maxwell taught, \u201cEach assertion of a righteous desire, each act of service, and each act of worship, however small and incremental, adds to our spiritual momentum.\u201d<a class=\"note-ref\" href=\"#note14\"><sup class=\"marker\">14<\/sup><\/a> Truly, it is by small, simple, and, yes, even just 1 percent things that great things can be brought to pass.<a class=\"note-ref\" href=\"#note15\"><sup class=\"marker\">15<\/sup><\/a> Ultimate victory is 100 percent certain, \u201cafter all we can do,\u201d<a class=\"note-ref\" href=\"#note16\"><sup class=\"marker\">16<\/sup><\/a> through the might, merits, and mercy of our Lord and Savior, Jesus Christ. I so testify in the name of Jesus Christ, amen.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<footer class=\"notes\">\n<p class=\"title\" data-aid=\"147980057\" id=\"note_title1\">Notes<\/p>\n<ol class=\"decimal\" data-type=\"marker\" start=\"1\">\n<li data-marker=\"1.\" id=\"note1\" data-full-marker=\"1.\">\n<p data-aid=\"1479